==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|freyght|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|dum}} {{term|vracht|lang=dum}}, {{etyl|gml}} {{term|vrecht||cost of transport|lang=gml}}, ultimately from {{proto|Germanic|title=|fra-|pos=intensive prefix|lang=en}} + {{proto|Germanic|aihtiz|possession|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|eiḱ-|to possess|lang=en}}, equivalent to {{prefix|for|aught}}. Cognate with {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|freht|frēht|earnings|lang=goh}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|æht|ǣht|sc=Latinx|owndom|lang=ang}}. More at {{l|en|for-}}, {{l|en|own}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|frāt}}, {{IPA|/freɪt/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/freIt/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪt}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# [[payment|Payment]] for transportation.
#: ''The '''freight''' was more expensive for cars than for coal.''
# [[goods|Goods]] or [[item]]s in [[transport]].
#: ''The '''freight''' shifted and the trailer turned over on the highway.''
# Transport of goods.
#: ''They shipped it ordinary '''freight''' to spare the expense.''

